als for new products andor new production processes development of innovative process steps and introduction of new technology interface between rd analytical and plant technology departments in order to develop and transfer product and process knowhow  supporting the plant in troubleshooting manufacturing issues and process related excursions identify innovative technology that will improve the quality and cost of products and processes job requirements master or phd degree in chemical engineering relevant work experience or a pdeng degree is a plus interest in process technology and physical transport phenomena affinity with rd and process equipment proactive convincing and decisive flexible and stress resistant analytical solutiondriven and pragmatic good communication skills strong knowledge of application of statistical techniques for data analysis process control and validation strong laboratory skills handson mindset good understanding of design of experiments with proven ability to apply within chemical operations good knowledge of problem solving  root cause analysis methodologies fluent english good knowledge of dutch responsibilities experience educationdoctorate chemical engineering masters chemical engineering required certification skills languagedutch required english required apply not ready to apply share with httpwwwjobsnetjobsalbemarlecorpenusjobnetherlandsprocessdevelopmentengineerjgvnvppqm process development engineer job snapshot employee type fulltime location amsterdam noordholland job type engineering experience not specified date posted  about us albemarle is a leading specialty chemical company providing innovative chemistry solutions to customers in over  countries around the world we are committed to creating value for our shareholders customers and employees while continually striving for excellence by doing the right things the right way at albemarle weve built a thriving international business by envisioning a limitless future and put